This is one of my favourite place for coffee, ofcourse during mostly during month start, not month end. Yeah Starbucks is a brand but it is pricey and from past few years prices of coffee and other things have gone up considerably.

Coffee is good, but can be better given the premium they charge. The cold coffee was also ok types, I expected them to add sugar in the cold coffee atleast, We spent almost 20 minutes and 4-5 sachets of sugar to make it taste better. Pretty difficult to mix sugar in cold coffee, they should know about it.

The sandwich was also okayish, newyork cheese cake was yummy. So overall it was ok experience. I will definitely rethink going Starbucks next time and give chance to new independent cafes, that gave quality for the price.

This space is good for couples and big groups. I was missing the light music and the cosy sittings that other Starbucks outlets in Pune offers.

I know most of u are big fans of the chain, but I'm not really a fan. I think it's overpriced, the coffee is mediocre, and the atmosphere is too pretentious for my taste.

I remember one time when we were all out with my friends wife, and she insisted that we go to Starbucks. I didn't really want to go, but I didn't want to be rude. So we went, and I ended up spending way too much money on a cup of coffee that my wife, me or that friend of mine didn't even like.

I then realized that that there are fans of this place who mostly I feel are just being pretentious. Lousy cow thinks that drinking Starbucks makes her seem more sophisticated, but I think it just makes her look like a snob.

There is a Barista Aaron and these two ladies - Preeti and Rajni. If you go to Starbucks at Amanora Mall please take out a minute or two to talk to them. I have never met more friendly people in Starbucks before (pan-India).

They customise any given drink as per my requirement which is intense coffee to keep me awake. Their tone is welcoming, affable and positive. These women maintain not only the decorum but also the positivity of the cafe.

I go here at least once a week to study or for work and these people make it worth the visit.

Anyway, here are some of my favourite drinks:
- Flat White if you're looking for something (only) strong
- Flat White with hazelnut flavour if you're looking for something strong+sweet. You won't need to go for the sugar sachets.
- Signature hot chocolate is a must must have!! I can't stress that enough.
- Latte has more milk
- Cappuccino has less milk but more froth
- White chocolate mocha is also a less tried drink

Sweet delicacies:
- cookies are only for people with sweet-tooth
- if you like sweet but not too much the blueberry muffins and chocolate truffle would be a good choice
- the red velvet here is better than other bakeries. I have never tasted it but the staff highly recommends it

Whether you're in the mood for a light breakfast or a quick bite to eat, their menu provides a variety of options.
